{"error":0,"message":null,"data":{"name":"Newsletter &#8211; Send awesome emails from WordPress","plugin":"newsletter","link":"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/plugins\/newsletter\/","latest":"1782132840","closed":0,"vulnerability":[{"uuid":"072c502c7eaec79dd08b4290c6475b187a4e88deef37143e6d54cb54deeb570b","name":"Newsletter &#8211; Send awesome emails from WordPress [newsletter] < 6.8.2","description":null,"operator":{"min_version":null,"min_operator":null,"max_version":"6.8.2","max_operator":"lt","unfixed":"0","closed":"0"},"source":[{"id":"CVE-2020-35932","name":"CVE-2020-35932","link":"https:\/\/www.cve.org\/CVERecord?id=CVE-2020-35932","description":"[en] Insecure Deserialization in the Newsletter plugin before 6.8.2 for WordPress allows authenticated remote attackers with minimal privileges (such as subscribers) to use the tpnc_render AJAX action to inject arbitrary PHP objects via the options[inline_edits] parameter. NOTE: exploitability depends on PHP objects that might be present with certain other plugins or themes.","date":"2021-01-01"},{"id":"d356be990a528a7034941f6222921487805a408f","name":"Newsletter <= 6.8.1 - Authenticated PHP Object Injection","link":"https:\/\/www.wordfence.com\/threat-intel\/vulnerabilities\/wordpress-plugins\/newsletter\/newsletter-681-authenticated-php-object-injection","description":"Insecure Deserialization in the Newsletter plugin before 6.8.2 for WordPress allows authenticated remote attackers with minimal privileges (such as subscribers) to use the tpnc_render AJAX action to inject arbitrary PHP objects via the options[inline_edits] parameter. NOTE: exploitability depends on PHP objects that might be present with certain other plugins or themes.","date":"2020-08-02"},{"id":"f27991d8-8834-4cb2-84e1-bad74fa94a5e","name":"Newsletter &lt; 6.8.2 - Authenticated PHP Object Injection","link":"https:\/\/wpscan.com\/vulnerability\/f27991d8-8834-4cb2-84e1-bad74fa94a5e","description":"The &lsquo;restore_options_from_request&lsquo; function called by the AJAX function &lsquo;tnpc_render_callback&lsquo; runs &lsquo;unserialize&rsquo; directly on &lsquo;$options[&#039;inline_edits&#039;]&rsquo; which is provided by user input in the $_POST[&lsquo;options&rsquo;] parameter. This creates the potential for an Object Injection vulnerability. For example, a user with minimal permissions, such as a subscriber, could send a POST request to wp-admin\/admin-ajax.php with the &lsquo;action&rsquo; parameter set to &lsquo;tpnc_render&rsquo; and the &lsquo;options[inline_edits]&rsquo; parameter set to a serialized object.\r\n\r\nAlthough the Newsletter plugin does not itself use any magic methods such as __destruct or __wakeup which could be used to complete a POP chain, these methods are common in 3rd party libraries and other plugins, and as such could be used as part of a POP chain which could be used to execute arbitrary code or have other critical-severity impacts.","date":null}],"impact":{"cvss":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:L\/PR:L\/UI:N\/S:U\/C:H\/I:H\/A:H","av":"n","ac":"l","pr":"l","ui":"n","s":"u","c":"h","i":"h","a":"h","score":"8.8","severity":"h","exploitable":"2.8","impact":"5.9"},"cvss3":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:L\/PR:L\/UI:N\/S:U\/C:H\/I:H\/A:H","score":"8.8","severity":"high","av":"network","ac":"low","pr":"low","ui":"none","s":"unchanged","c":"high","i":"high","a":"high","exploitable":"2.8","impact":"5.9"},"cwe":[{"cwe":"CWE-502","name":"Deserialization of Untrusted Data","description":"The product deserializes untrusted data without sufficiently ensuring that the resulting data will be valid."}]}},{"uuid":"c9cf2472439d689123553db8dc8249a886c0feb3bfb6bb95a8e91c4a101de8c4","name":"Newsletter &#8211; Send awesome emails from WordPress [newsletter] < 6.8.2","description":null,"operator":{"min_version":null,"min_operator":null,"max_version":"6.8.2","max_operator":"lt","unfixed":"0","closed":"0"},"source":[{"id":"CVE-2020-35933","name":"CVE-2020-35933","link":"https:\/\/www.cve.org\/CVERecord?id=CVE-2020-35933","description":"[en] A Reflected Authenticated Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the Newsletter plugin before 6.8.2 for WordPress allows remote attackers to trick a victim into submitting a tnpc_render AJAX request containing either JavaScript in an options parameter, or a base64-encoded JSON string containing JavaScript in the encoded_options parameter.","date":"2021-01-01"},{"id":"502abc23723d30a8f9d706f92abfd12ee982690f","name":"WordPress Newsletter plugin <= 6.8.1 - Authenticated Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability","link":"https:\/\/patchstack.com\/database\/wordpress\/plugin\/newsletter\/vulnerability\/wordpress-newsletter-plugin-6-8-1-authenticated-cross-site-scripting-xss-vulnerability","description":"Authenticated Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability found by Ramuel Gall in WordPress Newsletter plugin (versions <= 6.8.1).","date":"2020-08-03"},{"id":"f25a8d14a73cd460f9ac556b26d0d4bb4e8e76b8","name":"Newsletter <= 6.8.1 - Reflected Cross-Site Scripting","link":"https:\/\/www.wordfence.com\/threat-intel\/vulnerabilities\/wordpress-plugins\/newsletter\/newsletter-681-reflected-cross-site-scripting","description":"A Reflected Authenticated Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the Newsletter plugin before 6.8.2 for WordPress allows remote attackers to trick a victim into submitting a tnpc_render AJAX request containing either JavaScript in an options parameter, or a base64-encoded JSON string containing JavaScript in the encoded_options parameter.","date":"2020-08-03"},{"id":"6e4e22dd-d04a-4cce-9f45-2592158449e6","name":"Newsletter &lt; 6.8.2 - Authenticated Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)","link":"https:\/\/wpscan.com\/vulnerability\/6e4e22dd-d04a-4cce-9f45-2592158449e6","description":"Newsletter suffers from an Authenticated Reflected Cross-Site Scripting(XSS) vulnerability via the &lsquo;tnpc_render&rsquo; AJAX action found in newsletter\/emails\/emails.php. Due to how the corresponding &lsquo;tnpc_render_callback&lsquo; function decodes input via the &lsquo;restore_options_from_request&rsquo; function and renders them via the &lsquo;render_block&rsquo; function, it is possible to use this function to render arbitrary JavaScript in several ways when sending a POST request to wp-admin\/admin-ajax.php with the &lsquo;action&rsquo; POST parameter set to &lsquo;tnpc_render&rsquo;:\r\n\r\nIn an array element of the &lsquo;options&rsquo; parameter - for example, by sending a request with the &lsquo;b&rsquo; parameter set to &lsquo;html&rsquo;, and the &lsquo;options[html]&rsquo; parameter set to arbitrary JavaScript\r\n\r\nIn the &lsquo;encoded_options&rsquo; parameter - for example by sending a request with the &lsquo;b&rsquo; parameter set to &lsquo;html&rsquo;, the &lsquo;options&rsquo; parameter set an empty array (e.g. options[]=&amp;) and the &lsquo;encoded_options&rsquo; parameter set to a base64-encoded JSON string containing the arbitrary JavaScript in the &lsquo;html&rsquo; element.","date":null}],"impact":{"cvss":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:L\/PR:L\/UI:R\/S:C\/C:L\/I:L\/A:L","av":"n","ac":"l","pr":"l","ui":"r","s":"c","c":"l","i":"l","a":"l","score":"6.5","severity":"m","exploitable":"2.3","impact":"3.7"},"cvss3":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:L\/PR:L\/UI:R\/S:C\/C:L\/I:L\/A:L","score":"6.5","severity":"medium","av":"network","ac":"low","pr":"low","ui":"required","s":"changed","c":"low","i":"low","a":"low","exploitable":"2.3","impact":"3.7"},"cwe":[{"cwe":"CWE-79","name":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","description":"The product does not neutralize or incorrectly neutralizes user-controllable input before it is placed in output that is used as a web page that is served to other users."}]}},{"uuid":"9f0dc31527ff23326e3cc232d41ae21726da1632bdfa578a516cf3c17df54c1c","name":"Newsletter &#8211; Send awesome emails from WordPress [newsletter] < 6.5.4","description":null,"